{"title":"**Why animal sounds?** <br> ... and why R?","markdown":{"yaml":{"author":"Marcelo Araya-Salas","toc":false,"number-sections":false,"format":{"revealjs":{"self-contained":false,"incremental":false,"footer":"Marcelo Araya-Salas | Bioacoustic data analysis with R 2024","theme":["custom.scss"],"slide-number":"c/t","show-slide-number":"all","hash-type":"number","preview-links":false}}},"headingText":"**Why animal sounds?** <br> ... and why R?","headingAttr":{"id":"","classes":[],"keyvalue":[["background-color","#e0f3a8"]]},"containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\n\n \n\n<center><font size=\"6\">Marcelo Araya-Salas PhD</font></center>\n\n<center><font size=\"6\">*Neuroscience Research Center*</font></center>\n\n<center><font size=\"6\">*University of Costa Rica*</font></center>\n\n \n\n \n\n<!-- <center><img src=\"images/ucr_cin.png\" width=\"600px\"/></center>  -->\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n## **Animal acoustic signals** {.center background-color=\"black\"}\n\n<center>\n\n<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"600\" src=\"images/lbh_singing_30fps.mp4\" allowtransparency=\"true\" style=\"background: #000000;\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen>\n\n</iframe>\n\n</center>\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n## **Animal acoustic signals**\n\n<center>\n\n<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"500\" src=\"images/house-wren.mp4\" title=\"YouTube video player\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen>\n\n</iframe>\n\n</center>\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n## **Common research questions**\n\n::: incremental\n-   How animal acoustic signals vary in space and time? why?\n\n-   What is their function?\n\n-   What socio-ecological factors favor the evolution of specific features?\n\n-   How the transmission properties of the environment have shaped signal structure?\n:::\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n## **Acoustic analysis workflow**\n\n<center><img src=\"images/bioacoustic_research_diagram.png\" height=\"100%\" width=\"800px\"/></center>\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n## **Why bioacoustics in R?**\n\n::: incremental\n-   Improves reproducibility of research\n\n-   Involves a deeper understanding of the structure of our study systems\n\n-   Allows conducting analyses that better fit our research questions and study systems\n\n-   Democratizes access to scientific resources\n:::\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n## **Course outline** {background-color=\"#e0f3a8\"}\n\n::: incremental\n-   Tutorials with combinations of theoretical background, demonstrations and proofs of concept using R code\n- Self-learning practices on their own acoustic data or supplied example data\n-   Additional practices and readings assigned after each session (optional)\n:::\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":"\n\n# **Why animal sounds?** <br> ... and why R? {background-color=\"#e0f3a8\"}\n\n \n\n<center><font size=\"6\">Marcelo Araya-Salas PhD</font></center>\n\n<center><font size=\"6\">*Neuroscience Research Center*</font></center>\n\n<center><font size=\"6\">*University of Costa Rica*</font></center>\n\n \n\n \n\n<!-- <center><img src=\"images/ucr_cin.png\" width=\"600px\"/></center>  -->\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n## **Animal acoustic signals** {.center background-color=\"black\"}\n\n<center>\n\n<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"600\" src=\"images/lbh_singing_30fps.mp4\" allowtransparency=\"true\" style=\"background: #000000;\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen>\n\n</iframe>\n\n</center>\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n## **Animal acoustic signals**\n\n<center>\n\n<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"500\" src=\"images/house-wren.mp4\" title=\"YouTube video player\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen>\n\n</iframe>\n\n</center>\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n## **Common research questions**\n\n::: incremental\n-   How animal acoustic signals vary in space and time? why?\n\n-   What is their function?\n\n-   What socio-ecological factors favor the evolution of specific features?\n\n-   How the transmission properties of the environment have shaped signal structure?\n:::\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n## **Acoustic analysis workflow**\n\n<center><img src=\"images/bioacoustic_research_diagram.png\" height=\"100%\" width=\"800px\"/></center>\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n## **Why bioacoustics in R?**\n\n::: incremental\n-   Improves reproducibility of research\n\n-   Involves a deeper understanding of the structure of our study systems\n\n-   Allows conducting analyses that better fit our research questions and study systems\n\n-   Democratizes access to scientific resources\n:::\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n## **Course outline** {background-color=\"#e0f3a8\"}\n\n::: incremental\n-   Tutorials with combinations of theoretical background, demonstrations and proofs of concept using R code\n- Self-learning practices on their own acoustic data or supplied example data\n-   Additional practices and readings assigned after each session (optional)\n:::\n"},"formats":{"revealjs":{"identifier":{"display-name":"RevealJS","target-format":"revealjs","base-format":"revealjs"},"execute":{"fig-width":10,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","